<br>
I have my own doubts as to whether the average (note average) level 60 wizard can solo him without exploits (such as warp pulls to zone) but that is neither here nor there.<br>
<br>
This fight and this part of the epic is nothing short of a disgrace - it is everything that Everquest is renown for. There is no fucking way you should have to fight the same encounter again and again and again - it is nothing short of utterly incompetant design and if Sony/Verant actually defended the drop rate as has been described above (I personally have no evidence that they have done so) then they are wankers - one and all!!<br>
<br>
Make Phinny harder sure, make him a LOT harder but FFS stop this pointless crappy timesink!!<br>
<br>
I want an epic that is truly epic - I want it to take ages, preferably over all the levels (20-55 minimum), I want it to be HARD, but I want to feel I am making progress, I would rather fight 50 different mobs and actually get the item I needed each time than fight Phinny 50 times and get the single item I need on the 50th occassion. <br>
<br>
The wizard epic is a pile of shite - it only requires 3 items (this in itself is anything but 'epic') - but you have an incredibly rare drop, a golem who is never fucking up 'cos everybody and his wife has killed him 24 hours before you can go get him (why the fuck can't we have a spawned situation like Fedeydar(sp?) - of the 3 only VS is well balanced - for the guilds and levels who go for him at he is a challenge (a pretty steep one at that) and his epic drop rate is perfectly acceptable.<br>
<br>
I'd say that the Mage epic was a perfect example of a good epic - 'cept they also have the damn idiotic Phinny grief too!!<br>
<br>
